Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Cut the @sweet potato{2} in half lengthways and then cut each half into eight wedges. They need to be roughly the size of your index finger. Place the wedges on a #baking tray{} with @oil{2%tbsp}, season with @salt{1/2%tsp} and half of the @Mexican spice{1%portion}. Mix well to ensure all the wedges are coated. Bake in the oven for ~{25-30%minutes} or until golden and cooked through.

> Get the kids in the kitchen to massage the sweet potatoes with the oil, salt and Mexican spice.

While the wedges cook, marinate the @flank steak{3} in the remaining @Mexican spice{1%portion}, and @oil{1%tbsp}.

Peel and cut the @red onion{1}(peeled) in half through the root and slice thinly into half moon shapes. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and thinly slice. Peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{1}. Separate the @coriander{5%sprigs} leaves from the stalks and chop the stalks as small as you can. Keep the leaves for later. Remove the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}, separate and chop the leaves into 1cm strips.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat and let the pan get very hot. Fry the steaks for ~{3%minutes} on each side for medium rare or cook for a minute longer on each side for medium.

> Don't be tempted to turn the steak before the 3 mins are up! They will taste so much better if left to scorch!

Remove the steaks from the pan and allow them to relax on your #chopping board{}. Keep the pan on the heat and stir-fry the onion and peppers for ~{3%minutes}. Add the garlic and coriander stalks and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Remove from the heat. Slice the steak into thin strips ½cm wide.

> When slicing steak, always cut against the grain of the piece of meat.

Now get ready to assemble the tortillas! Take a @corn tortilla{8} and spread 1/2 tsp of @garlic mayonnaise{4%tsp} onto the bottom half of a tortilla. Top with some of the onion and pepper, some baby gem lettuce and a layer of steak strips. Finish with a few coriander leaves and then roll the tortilla. Repeat until you have two tortillas each.

Serve with a generous pile of sweet potato wedges and a dollop of garlic mayonnaise. Yum!